# SliceMatic — Cursor Rules

## 🧠 Start Every Session by Reading the Wiki

The wiki at `wiki/` (relative to repo root `Slicematic/`) is the shared brain.
**Always read `wiki/index.md` and `wiki/handoff.md` before starting any task.**

## ⚡ Non-Negotiable Rules

### Dual-File Rule (CRITICAL)
Two files must ALWAYS stay in sync for shared UI sections:
- `FullStack/components/SliceMaticStage3.tsx`
- `FullStack/app/admin-dashboard/page.tsx`

Shared sections: `renderCustomerAccount()`, 3-info-cards, auth views, order history widget.
**If you edit one, you MUST edit the other.**

### CSS Rules
- **NO Tailwind** — not a single class
- All CSS goes in `FullStack/app/globals.css`
- Design tokens: use existing `:root` variables (--tomato, --bg, --line, --radius, etc.)
- Check `wiki/css-system.md` for existing layout classes before writing new CSS
- The `.account-grid` uses `repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr))` — 3 equal columns

### TypeScript & State
- Types are in `lib/types.ts` — never redeclare inline
- Global state via Zustand (`lib/store.ts`) — sessionStorage persisted
- Auth state via manual sessionStorage keys — see `wiki/auth-flows.md`
- Never use `localStorage` for session data

### Supabase
- Guard all DB calls: `if (!hasSupabaseEnv()) return fallback`
- Fall back to `lib/seed-data.ts` for menu data

### Business Rules (lib/pricing.ts)
- GST = 18%, Bulk discount = 10% at qty ≥ 5, Max qty = 10
- Bill order: subtotal → discount → taxable → GST → delivery → total
- Never change these constants without reading the PRD

## 📋 After Every Session

1. Add entry to `FullStack/CHANGELOG.md`
2. Update `wiki/handoff.md`

## 🚫 Never Do

- Never use Tailwind
- Never hardcode menu prices or item names
- Never use localStorage for auth
- Never let exceptions bubble to the UI uncaught
- Never modify `gradio-MVP/` or `GRADIO-MVP-2/` for Stage 3 work

## Commands

```bash
# Working dir: FullStack/
npm run dev       # port 3000
npm run test      # vitest
npm run build     # production
```
